{{Refimprove|date=June 2015}} {{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Fatmir Gjata | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = Fatmir Gjata.jpg | image_size = 300px | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date|1922|09|22}} | birth_place = [[Korçë]], [[Principality of Albania]] | death_date = 1989 | death_place = [[Tirana]], [[People's Socialist Republic of Albania]] | resting_place = | occupation = Writer, journalist | language = | nationality = Albanian | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = [[Maxim Gorky Literature Institute]] | alma_mater = | period = | genre = Fiction ([[novel]]s, stories, screenplays), [[revolutionary song]]s | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = [[Socialist Realism]] | notableworks = <!-- or: | notablework = --> | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }} '''Fatmir Gjata''' (1922&ndash;1989) was a prominent Albanian writer of [[Socialist Realism]]. He is considered one of the top two Albanian novelists (next to [[Ismail Kadare]]).<ref>{{citation| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=loYxAQAAIAAJ&q=fatmir+gjata&dq=fatmir+gjata&hl=en&sa=X&ei=njVeVfbsMsG2sAG5soDoAQ&ved=0CDIQ6AEwBDge| series=Collier's encyclopedia: with bibliography and index|volume=I| page=473| author=Bernard Johnston| year=1992| title=Albania| publisher=Macmillan Educational Co|location=New York| oclc=25518767}}</ref>{{Failed verification|date=June 2015}}
==Life== Fatmir Gjata was born in [[Korçë]], [[Albania]] in 1922.<ref name="IAP">{{citation|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZqtiAAAAMAAJ&q=fatmir+gjata&dq=fatmir+gjata&hl=en&sa=X&ei=njVeVfbsMsG2sAG5soDoAQ&ved=0CEUQ6AEwCDge| pages=116–117| title=Gjurmime albanologjike| series=Seria e shkencave filologjike| volume=15-16| location=Prishtina|year=1986| publisher=Instituti Albanologjik i Prishtines| oclc= 475280214}}</ref> His father Isuf Gjata was a teacher who joined the [[National Liberation Movement (Albania)|National Liberation Movement]] during [[World War II]] and fell in 1944. Fatmir Gjata studied in the [[Albanian National Lyceum|French Lyceum of Korçë]] and later he attended the [[Maxim Gorky Literature Institute]] in [[Moscow]]. As a communist and a poet, he wrote several poetry volumes during World War II and later, some of which would become known [[partisan songs]]. During the war he was in charge of a local illegal newspaper. He poetry was embroidered with march-style enthusiasm and solemn [[lexicology]].<ref name="IAP"/>
He would claim his place in Albanian literature during 1950-90 period with his novels,<ref>{{citation|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FPdRAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA1254&dq=fatmir+gjata&hl=en&sa=X&ei=gzVeVZDeG4SQsAHms4CwBw&ved=0CC0Q6AEwBDgU#v=onepage&q=fatmir%20gjata&f=false|page=1254| author=Paul Schellinger| publisher=Routledge| year=1998|isbn=1579580157 | title=Encyclopedia of the Novel}}</ref> theatrical plays, short story volumes and screenplays, some of which would turn into films such as [[Tana (film)|''Tana'']], the first Albanian movie.<ref>{{citation|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oZAHAQAAIAAJ&q=fatmir+gjata&dq=fatmir+gjata&hl=en&sa=X&ei=iEleVebLCOTOyQPVkYDQBw&ved=0CD8Q6AEwBzg8|language=Albanian| title=Filmi shqiptar| publisher=8 Nëntori| author=Fisnik Pulaj| page=10|oclc= 5615835}}</ref>
Fatmir Gjata is also known for directing some of the most important institutes of art and culture in [[Communist Albania]]. He served as Chairman of the Committee for Arts and Culture, member of the [[Albanian League of Writers and Artists]], [[editor-in-chief]] for 25 years of ''[[Nëntori]]'' literary magazine, journalist, and member of the collegial council for other press organs such as ''[[Zëri i Popullit]]'', ''[[Drita (magazine)|Drita]]'', ''[[Ylli (magazine)|Ylli]]'', ''[[Hosteni]]'', etc. His work has been translated into other languages.
Many of his works received national prizes in Albania, such as "Republic's First Prize", "Order of the Flag of First Class", etc.
He died in [[Tirana]], in 1989.
==Prominent works== *''Këneta'' (The swamp), 1959 (novel) *''Këshilltarët'' (The councelors), 1979 (novel) *'' Në pragun e jetës'' (At the doorstep of life), 1960 (short stories) *'' Fillim pranvere'' (Spring eve), 1977 (novel) *''Brezat'' (Generations), 1968 (novel) *''Tana'', 1958 (novel) *''Përmbysja'' (The overthrow), 1954 (novel) *'' Në tokën kineze-kujtime dhe tregime'' (In the Chinese land - memoirs and stories), 1958 (co-author with [[Sterjo Spasse]]) *''Me një torbë me fishekë: ditar'' (With a bagful of bullets: diary), 1982 (memoirs) *''Rrugës mes njerëzve të thjeshtë'' (In the streets among simple people), 1969 (stories collection) * ''Heronjt e vigut'' (Heroes of Vig), 1959 (story) * ''Armiqtë'' (The enemies), 1966 (novel)
