{{Infobox language |name=Ngiemboon |nativename=''Ngyɛmbɔɔŋ'' |states=[[Cameroon]] |region=[[Western Province, Cameroon|Province de l'Ouest]], [[Bamboutos]] |speakers=250,000 |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Grassfields languages|Grassfields]] |fam6=[[Eastern Grassfields languages|Eastern]] |fam7=[[Bamileke languages|Bamiléké]] |fam8=Bamboutos |iso3=nnh |glotto=ngie1241 |glottorefname=Ngiemboon }}
The '''Ngiemboon (N'Jhamboon) language''', ''Ngyɛmbɔɔŋ'', is one of a dozen [[Bamileke languages]] spoken in [[Cameroon]].
